      "content": "A healthy society requires a delicate balance, but the fear of being silenced is fundamentally detrimental to genuine progress. While holding people accountable for harmful actions is crucial, an environment of fear where people are afraid to speak at all halts the necessary debate for social improvement. Therefore, the ability to engage in robust, even offensive, debate is arguably more vital for long-term societal health than achieving immediate consensus.",
      "source": "target",
